  "root_text": {
    "sn11.2:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 11.2 ",
    "sn11.2:0.2": "1. Paṭhamavagga ",
    "sn11.2:0.3": "Susīmasutta ",
    "sn11.2:1.1": "Sāvatthiyaṁ. ",
    "sn11.2:1.2": "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi: ",
    "sn11.2:1.3": "“bhikkhavo”ti. ",
    "sn11.2:1.4": "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṁ. ",
    "sn11.2:1.5": "Bhagavā etadavoca: ",
    "sn11.2:2.1": "“Bhūtapubbaṁ, bhikkhave, asurā deve abhiyaṁsu. ",
    "sn11.2:2.2": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṁ devaputtaṁ āmantesi: ",
    "sn11.2:2.3": "‘ete, tāta susīma, asurā deve abhiyanti. ",
    "sn11.2:2.4": "Gaccha, tāta susīma, asure paccuyyāhī’ti. ",
    "sn11.2:2.5": "‘Evaṁ, bhaddantavā’ti kho, bhikkhave, susīmo devaputto sakkassa devānamindassa paṭissutvā pamādaṁ āpādesi. ",
    "sn11.2:2.6": "Dutiyampi kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṁ devaputtaṁ āmantesi …pe… ",
    "sn11.2:2.7": "dutiyampi pamādaṁ āpādesi. ",
    "sn11.2:2.8": "Tatiyampi kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṁ devaputtaṁ āmantesi …pe… ",
    "sn11.2:2.9": "tatiyampi pamādaṁ āpādesi. ",
    "sn11.2:2.10": "Atha kho, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo susīmaṁ devaputtaṁ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: ",
    "sn11.2:3.1": "‘Anuṭṭhahaṁ avāyāmaṁ, ",
    "sn11.2:3.2": "sukhaṁ yatrādhigacchati; ",
    "sn11.2:3.3": "Susīma tattha gacchāhi, ",
    "sn11.2:3.4": "mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti. ",
    "sn11.2:4.1": "‘Alasvassa anuṭṭhātā, ",
    "sn11.2:4.2": "na ca kiccāni kāraye; ",
    "sn11.2:4.3": "Sabbakāmasamiddhassa, ",
    "sn11.2:4.4": "taṁ me sakka varaṁ disā’ti. ",
    "sn11.2:5.1": "‘Yatthālaso anuṭṭhātā, ",
    "sn11.2:5.2": "accantaṁ sukhamedhati; ",
    "sn11.2:5.3": "Susīma tattha gacchāhi, ",
    "sn11.2:5.4": "mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti. ",
    "sn11.2:6.1": "‘Akammunā devaseṭṭha, ",
    "sn11.2:6.2": "sakka vindemu yaṁ sukhaṁ; ",
    "sn11.2:6.3": "Asokaṁ anupāyāsaṁ, ",
    "sn11.2:6.4": "taṁ me sakka varaṁ disā’ti. ",
    "sn11.2:7.1": "‘Sace atthi akammena, ",
    "sn11.2:7.2": "koci kvaci na jīvati; ",
    "sn11.2:7.3": "Nibbānassa hi so maggo, ",
    "sn11.2:7.4": "susīma tattha gacchāhi; ",
    "sn11.2:7.5": "Mañca tattheva pāpayā’ti. ",
    "sn11.2:8.1": "So hi nāma, bhikkhave, sakko devānamindo sakaṁ puññaphalaṁ upajīvamāno devānaṁ tāvatiṁsānaṁ issariyādhipaccaṁ rajjaṁ kārento uṭṭhānavīriyassa vaṇṇavādī bhavissati. ",
    "sn11.2:8.2": "Idha kho taṁ, bhikkhave, sobhetha, yaṁ tumhe evaṁ svākkhāte dhammavinaye pabbajitā samānā uṭṭhaheyyātha ghaṭeyyātha vāyameyyātha appattassa pattiyā, anadhigatassa adhigamāya, asacchikatassa sacchikiriyāyā”ti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn11.2:0.1": "Linked Discourses 11.2 ",
    "sn11.2:0.2": "Chapter One ",
    "sn11.2:0.3": "With Susīma ",
    "sn11.2:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn11.2:1.2": "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants, ",
    "sn11.2:1.3": "“Mendicants!” ",
    "sn11.2:1.4": "“Venerable sir,” they replied. ",
    "sn11.2:1.5": "The Buddha said this: ",
    "sn11.2:2.1": "“Once upon a time, mendicants, the titans marched against the gods. ",
    "sn11.2:2.2": "Then Sakka, lord of gods, addressed the godling Susīma, ",
    "sn11.2:2.3": "‘Dear Susīma, the titans march against the gods! ",
    "sn11.2:2.4": "Go, and march against the titans!’ ",
    "sn11.2:2.5": "‘Yes, lord,’ replied Susīma. But he fell into negligence. ",
    "sn11.2:2.6": "For a second time … ",
    "sn11.2:2.7": "",
    "sn11.2:2.8": "For a third time … ",
    "sn11.2:2.9": "",
    "sn11.2:2.10": "Then Sakka addressed the godling Susīma in verse: ",
    "sn11.2:3.1": "‘Susīma, go to that place ",
    "sn11.2:3.2": "where you can achieve happiness ",
    "sn11.2:3.3": "without working for it or trying hard—",
    "sn11.2:3.4": "and take me with you!’ ",
    "sn11.2:4.1": "‘That a lazy man who does no work, ",
    "sn11.2:4.2": "and doesn’t do his duty, ",
    "sn11.2:4.3": "should fulfill all his desires: ",
    "sn11.2:4.4": "Sakka, render me this boon!’ ",
    "sn11.2:5.1": "‘Susīma, go to that place ",
    "sn11.2:5.2": "where a lazy man who does no work ",
    "sn11.2:5.3": "prospers in unending happiness—",
    "sn11.2:5.4": "and take me with you!’ ",
    "sn11.2:6.1": "‘O Sakka, first among gods, ",
    "sn11.2:6.2": "that we might find the happiness ",
    "sn11.2:6.3": "that’s sorrowless, unstressed: ",
    "sn11.2:6.4": "Sakka, render me this boon!’ ",
    "sn11.2:7.1": "‘If there exists anywhere a place ",
    "sn11.2:7.2": "where one can live happily without working, ",
    "sn11.2:7.3": "that surely would be extinguishment’s path! ",
    "sn11.2:7.4": "Susīma, go to that place ",
    "sn11.2:7.5": "and take me with you!’ ",
    "sn11.2:8.1": "Since, mendicants, even that Sakka, lord of gods—while living off of the fruit of his good deeds, and ruling as sovereign lord over these gods of the thirty-three—will speak in praise of initiative and energy, ",
    "sn11.2:8.2": "you can excel at this, for you who have gone forth in such a well explained teaching and training can try hard, strive, and make an effort to attain the unattained, achieve the unachieved, and realize the unrealized.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "sn11.2:2.2": "susīmaṁ → susimaṁ (sya-all, km, mr) "
  },
